  +   +
On the September 9, Tens of thousands of protesters gathered for what they called the "Friday of Correcting the Path"<ref>http://thedailynewsegypt.com/egypt/tens-of-thousands-flock-to-tahrir-to-correct-the-path.html</ref> or the "Correct the Path" in Suez, Alexandria, Cairo and other cities in absence of supporters of Islamic political movements<ref>http://www.sis.gov.eg/En/Story.aspx?sid=57825</ref>.
  +   +
The major demands of the Friday were relieving the [[Mansour el-Essawy]] (''The current [[Ministry of Interior (Egypt)|Minister of the Interior]]'')<ref>http://www.sis.gov.eg/En/Story.aspx?sid=57825</ref>, maintaining independence of the judiciary<ref>http://www.sis.gov.eg/En/Story.aspx?sid=57825</ref>, closing the Israeli embassy in Cairo, amending the laws of the People's Assembly and Shura Council<ref>http://www.sis.gov.eg/En/Story.aspx?sid=57825</ref> and stopping [[Human_rights_in_Egypt_under_the_Supreme_Council_of_the_Armed_Forces#Military_trials|military trials for civilians]] that started under the [[SCAF]].
  +   +
After gathering in Tahrir Square, the protest moved to [[Ministry of Interior (Egypt)|MOI]], then to [[Supreme Constitutional Court of Egypt]] and finally towards the Israeli embassy
The '''2011 Israeli embassy attack''' occurred on September 9, 2011 in Cairo Egypt when Egyptian protesters entered the Israeli Embassy after tearing down the wall surrounding the building that houses it.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://aljazeera.com/news/middleeast/2011/09/20119993150747146.html |title=Egyptians protest against military rule - Middle East |publisher=Al Jazeera English |date=2001-09-11 |accessdate=2011-09-10}}</ref> Police has fired tear gas into the crowds.<ref name="IsraeliEmbassy">{{cite web|author=From Mohamed Fadel Fahmy, For CNN |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2011/WORLD/meast/09/09/egypt.protests/index.html |title=Protesters in Egypt breach wall, enter Israeli Embassy - CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date= |accessdate=2011-09-10}}</ref>
